verbose_text: A study of biotin and chromium piccolinate supplementation of type 2 diabetic rats resulted in anti-diabetic effects, apparently preventing insulin resistance in skeletal muscle by an increase in the expression of the glucose transporter protein GLUT4 [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
